---
name: Fast Dialog Pipeline (Sync.so Multi-Pass Chain, v5)
description: compose-dialog-segments now dispatches N sequential Sync.so calls (one per speaker, each chained on the previous pass's output) instead of one segments[]+ASD call (which crashes lipsync-2-pro). Webhook chains via {advance: true}; per-pass payload uses single audio + single-coord ASD, NO segments[]. State stores passes[] + current_pass + total_passes. Single-speaker scenes still run as one pass.
type: feature
---

Engine: `engine_override = 'sync-segments'` (parallel to legacy `'cinematic-sync'`).

**Why multi-pass:** Sync.so `lipsync-2-pro` crashes (`An unknown error occurred`) when `segments[]` + `options.active_speaker_detection` are sent together. Dropping ASD makes the call complete but Sync.so picks audioâ†’face auto-mapping and routinely swaps speakers. The only stable multi-speaker pattern is v4's: one call per speaker with single-coord ASD, chained.

**Per-pass payload (no segments[]):**
```json
{
  "model": "lipsync-2-pro",
  "input": [
    { "type": "video", "url": "<prev pass output OR master plate>" },
    { "type": "audio", "url": "<speaker.track_url with silence between turns>" }
  ],
  "options": {
    "active_speaker_detection": {
      "auto_detect": false,
      "frame_number": <mid of first turn>,
      "coordinates": [x, y]
    }
  },
  "webhookUrl": "..."
}
```

**State model (`dialog_shots`):**
```ts
{
  version: 5, engine: "sync-segments", status: "rendering"|"done"|"failed",
  multi_pass: boolean, passes: PassState[],
  current_pass: number, total_passes: number,
  sync_job_id: string,         // CURRENT pass's job id (for webhook match)
  source_clip_url, total_sec, cost_credits, refunded,
  first_started_at, started_at, retry_count,
  final_url?: string,          // set only on last pass COMPLETED
}
```

**Webhook flow (sync-so-webhook v5 branch):**
- COMPLETED + more passes remain â†’ mark pass done, increment `current_pass`, fire-and-forget `compose-dialog-segments {scene_id, advance: true}`.
- COMPLETED + last pass â†’ re-host MP4 to ai-videos, set `clip_url`, `lip_sync_applied_at`, `twoshot_stage='complete'`.
- FAILED/transient + retry budget â†’ re-dispatch same pass via `{scene_id, retry: true}`.
- FAILED/non-retryable â†’ idempotent refund + `lip_sync_status='failed'`.

**Requirements:** every speaker MUST have `track_url` (compose-twoshot-audio output). Missing â†’ 422 + refund + clear error.

**Cost:** still `ceil(totalSec) * 9` credits charged ONCE upfront. All passes share the same budget (Sync.so bills per-pass internally, our user-facing price stays flat). `cost_credits` preserved across `retry=true` and `advance=true` dispatches.

**Progress bar (`usePipelineProgress.ts`):** when lipsync is terminal (done/failed) AND no master-render is running, `runSoftPercent` stops ramping toward `RUN_NOMINAL_SECONDS` and locks to `phaseOverall` (sum of weighted done phases). Eliminates the "still loading after 5 min" stuck-bar bug.

**Affected files:**
- `supabase/functions/compose-dialog-segments/index.ts` (multi-pass dispatch + advance branch)
- `supabase/functions/sync-so-webhook/index.ts` (advance vs finalize logic)
- `src/hooks/usePipelineProgress.ts` (waitingForExport cap)
